@tqchen  how to handle multiple outputs? i was trying `dropout` and `batchnorm`, both have multiple outputs.
In `RELAY_REGISTER_OP`, like `set_num_inputs`, do we have something like `set_num_outputs`?
I think currently `Array<Type>& types` will have only (inputs + one output)

@ashutoshparkhi 

This may not work for many cases as 'N' index value in _input_shapes may be -1 most of the times.
Alternative approach to have a concrete solution would be passing  graph level input shape to frontend and infer. Ref. https://github.com/srkreddy1238/tvm/commit/24665aef83d2287b331fac4718e62dcc11031f65 which I have done for ONNX.
